The directories za and zd contain the assembler and disassembler. These use
standard Rust/Cargo project layouts. To build, change into the directory and
run:

cargo build --release

This will create the executable ./target/debug/za (or zd). At the moment there
is no install procedure: either run the executables directly from the zdevtools
directory, or copy them somewhere in your $PATH.

There are Makefiles in the za and zd directories, but these are mostly an aid
for development, as they simply run "cargo build", which does non-optimized
debug builds.
